external_knowledge:
- "seasoned sailors" refers to users who have provided at least three feedback entries;
- "harbor" metaphorically refers to the unique identifier for each stream (stream_id);
- "sailboats" symbolically refer to the feedbacks given to streams, with a focus on the top three ratings for each stream;
- "navigated through" implies the action of providing feedback.

sql:
SELECT stream_id, AVG(quality_rating) as average_quality_rating
FROM stream_quality
GROUP BY stream_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS feedback_count
FROM user_feedback
WHERE user_id = 1234;
